Let's switch gears
to talk about ways

00:10:32.620 --> 00:10:36.500
to help you grow and
engage your audience.

00:10:36.500 --> 00:10:39.890
For those of you who are
building for the mobile web,

00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:42.040
we've heard your feedback
and the challenges you

00:10:42.040 --> 00:10:44.502
face in re-engaging your users.

00:10:44.502 --> 00:10:46.460
So we've been working
hard to extend the Chrome

00:10:46.460 --> 00:10:50.220
platform to bring native like
capabilities to help you drive

00:10:50.220 --> 00:10:53.670
re-engagement, with things
like push notifications even

00:10:53.670 --> 00:10:56.030
if the browser is
closed, the ability

00:10:56.030 --> 00:10:59.490
to add your app to the home
screen as if it was installed,

00:10:59.490 --> 00:11:03.810
and let users quickly re-access
that from their home screen.

00:11:03.810 --> 00:11:06.950
And also the ability to
work offline, and 2G support

00:11:06.950 --> 00:11:09.160
with service workers.

00:11:09.160 --> 00:11:11.940
Flipkart is a great
example of a company that

00:11:11.940 --> 00:11:14.340
has taken advantage of
some of these capabilities

00:11:14.340 --> 00:11:17.760
and created Flipkart Lite.

00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:20.450
We're going to have another
session later on today

00:11:20.450 --> 00:11:23.940
to go more in depth and
talk about these features.

00:11:23.940 --> 00:11:26.910
So be sure to stay
tuned for that.

00:11:26.910 --> 00:11:29.930
Another great example
of re-engagement

00:11:29.930 --> 00:11:32.570
is using push notifications.

00:11:32.570 --> 00:11:34.760
And this where Google
Cloud Messaging comes in.

00:11:34.760 --> 00:11:36.760
Google Cloud Messaging
lets you send messages

00:11:36.760 --> 00:11:38.620
from the cloud over
to your devices.

00:11:38.620 --> 00:11:40.890
And we've seen
incredible traction

00:11:40.890 --> 00:11:42.680
of developers using this.

00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:46.700
Today there over
150 billion messages

00:11:46.700 --> 00:11:49.940
that are processed each day
through Google Cloud Messaging.

00:11:49.940 --> 00:11:53.120
And there are over
750,000 apps using it.

00:11:53.120 --> 00:11:54.900
We're working really
hard to continue

00:11:54.900 --> 00:11:56.880
to improve the
scalability of this

00:11:56.880 --> 00:11:59.960
so that you don't have
to worry about managing

00:11:59.960 --> 00:12:02.120
your own infrastructure.

00:12:02.120 --> 00:12:05.890
And over the past months,
we've expanded the capabilities

00:12:05.890 --> 00:12:08.860
of Google Cloud Messaging
to not only work on Android,

00:12:08.860 --> 00:12:11.360
but also work on Chrome and iOS.

00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:14.480
And we've introduced a feature
called Topic Messaging, which

00:12:14.480 --> 00:12:18.320
lets you subscribe to multiple
devices to a specific topic

00:12:18.320 --> 00:12:21.900
and send a message specifically
targeting to those devices.

00:12:21.900 --> 00:12:24.440
For example, if you're
building a news app,

00:12:24.440 --> 00:12:26.670
you can send a
notification only to users

00:12:26.670 --> 00:12:29.610
that are interested in
sports and not in finance.

00:12:29.610 --> 00:12:32.460
Google handles this fan out
for and the scaling for you

00:12:32.460 --> 00:12:34.160
so you don't have to.

00:12:34.160 --> 00:12:36.500
Using Google Cloud
Messaging is free.

00:12:36.500 --> 00:12:39.040
And starting today
with Topic Messaging,

00:12:39.040 --> 00:12:40.895
we've also made this unlimited.

00:12:45.690 --> 00:12:47.510
Another great way to
drive re-engagement

00:12:47.510 --> 00:12:49.820
is by making your content
available through Google

00:12:49.820 --> 00:12:50.500
Search.

00:12:50.500 --> 00:12:52.660
And this is where app
indexing comes in.

00:12:52.660 --> 00:12:56.800
App indexing lets you index
your native app contents

00:12:56.800 --> 00:12:59.680
and make that discoverable
through Google Search.

00:12:59.680 --> 00:13:03.720
We see over $100 billion queries
per day in Google Search.

00:13:03.720 --> 00:13:05.710
So this is a really
great way to get

00:13:05.710 --> 00:13:11.260
in front of the users and drive
re-engagement of your app.

00:13:11.260 --> 00:13:13.790
So in addition to
your organic campaigns

00:13:13.790 --> 00:13:16.830
to drive re-engagement, another
great way to expand your reach

00:13:16.830 --> 00:13:18.070
is by using Google AdWords.

00:13:20.710 --> 00:13:24.290
With universal app campaigns
through Google AdWords,

00:13:24.290 --> 00:13:28.620
we help you reach users
across Google Search, YouTube,

00:13:28.620 --> 00:13:31.620
the Google Display
Network, and Google Play.

00:13:31.620 --> 00:13:33.630
Setting this up is very easy.

00:13:33.630 --> 00:13:36.910
You just have to create one
campaign, specify your budget,

00:13:36.910 --> 00:13:39.420
the amount you want to
pay to drive and install.

00:13:39.420 --> 00:13:41.400
And we would automatically
handle this for you

00:13:41.400 --> 00:13:44.800
to reach the most relevant users
across all of these channels.

